# Agent SOPs (Strands)

This project uses [Strands Agent SOPs](https://github.com/strands-agents/agent-sop) for structured, multi-step agent workflows.

## Slash commands

Type `/` in Cursor chat and pick a command:

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `/code-assist.sop` | TDD implementation (Explore → Plan → Code → Commit) |
| `/codebase-summary.sop` | Analyze and document the codebase |
| `/pdd.sop` | Prompt-driven development / design planning |
| `/code-task-generator.sop` | Break requirements into code tasks |
| `/eval.sop` | Agent evaluation workflow |

Commands live in `.cursor/commands/`. When invoked, prompt the user for required parameters before executing the workflow.

## Artifact directories

SOP outputs go under `.agents/`:

- `summary/` — codebase docs (commit)
- `planning/` — design docs (often commit)
- `tasks/` — generated code tasks (optional commit)
- `scratchpad/` — transient work (gitignored)

## MCP

The `agent-sops` MCP server is configured in `.cursor/mcp.json`. After config changes, reload MCP servers in **Cursor Settings → MCP**.

## Authoring new SOPs

Follow the format in `.cursor/rules/agent-sop-format.mdc`. Custom SOPs use the `.sop.md` extension.
